Paaliname MISSING reikmes:

ind <- with(duomenys, which(kaina=="MISSING" | amzius=="MISSING", rida=="MISSING" | galia=="MISSING", markesKodas=="MISSING"))
data <- duomenys[-ind,]

  1. Padalijame masyv du nesikertanius masyvus, juos pavadiname pagal uduot:
sub <- sample(nrow(data), floor(nrow(data) * 0.8))
trainSet <- data[sub, ]
testSet <- data[-sub, ]

trainSet$galia<-NULL

Gauname model:

  1. Tikriname liekan normalum:
hist(residuals(fit))

shapiro.test(fit$res) 
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  fit$res
## W = 0.85182, p-value = 1.413e-15
plot(residuals(fit), type="l", main="Modelio fit  paklaidos", ylab="fit paklaidos", xlab="Stebjimas", col=100)
abline(0,0)

Matome, kad paklaidos nra normalios (t rodo Shapiro testas), todl reikt model gerinti.

durbinWatsonTest(fit) #p reikm didesn nei 0.05, todl galime teigti, kad liekanos nekoreliuoja tarpusavyje.
##  lag Autocorrelation D-W Statistic p-value
##    1     -0.01145783      2.012346     0.9
##  Alternative hypothesis: rho != 0
